    "### <span style=\"font-family: Arial;font-size:1.2em;color:#3366ff\">Enveloped Model Evaluation Functions"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 32,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def evaluation(y_true, y_pred):\n",
    "    precision_micro = precision_score(y_true, y_pred, average='micro')\n",
    "    recall_micro = recall_score(y_true, y_pred, average='micro')\n",
    "    f1_micro = f1_score(y_true, y_pred, average='micro')\n",
    "    print(100*\"*\")\n",
    "    print(\"precision_micro:\",precision_micro,end=\"\\t\")\n",
    "    print(\"recall_micro:\",recall_micro,end=\"\\t\")\n",
    "    print(\"f1_micro:\",f1_micro)\n",
    "    precision_macro = precision_score(y_true, y_pred, average='macro')\n",
    "    recall_macro = recall_score(y_true, y_pred, average='macro')\n",
    "    f1_macro = f1_score(y_true, y_pred, average='macro')\n",
    "    print(\"precision_macro:\",precision_macro,end=\"\\t\")\n",
    "    print(\"recall_macro:\",recall_macro,end=\"\\t\")\n",
    "    print(\"f1_macro:\",f1_macro)\n",
    "    print(100*\"*\")\n",
    "\n",
    "    return f1_macro\n",
    "\n",
    "def model_eval(algo,X_train,y_train,X_test,y_test):\n",
    "    algo.fit(X_train,y_train)\n",
    "    y_train_ypred = algo.predict(X_train)\n",
    "    y_train_prob = algo.predict_proba(X_train)[:,-1]\n",
    "\n",
    "    #TEST\n",
    "    y_test_ypred = algo.predict(X_test)\n",
    "    y_test_prob = algo.predict_proba(X_test)[:,-1]\n",
    "    y_probas = algo.predict_proba(X_test)\n",
    "    auc = metrics.roc_auc_score(y_test,y_test_prob)\n",
    "    print(\"auc:\",auc)\n",
    "    acc_score = accuracy_score(y_test, y_test_ypred)\n",
    "    print(\"accuracy score:\",acc_score)\n",
    "    #Confussion Matrix\n",
    "    plot_confusion_matrix(algo, X_test, y_test)\n",
    "#   plt.show() \n",
    "    print('='*100)\n",
    "    # evaluation(y_test,y_test_ypred)\n",
    "    print('='*100)\n",
    "    print('Classification Report: \\n', classification_report(y_test, y_test_ypred, digits=3))\n",
    "    print('='*100)\n",
    "    \n",
    "#     ROC Curve\n",
    "    fpr,tpr,thresholds = roc_curve(y_test,y_test_prob)\n",
    "    skplt.metrics.plot_roc(y_test, y_probas,figsize=(8,6) )\n",
    "    \n",
    "#     PR Curve\n",
    "    skplt.metrics.plot_precision_recall(y_test, y_probas, figsize=(8,6))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def rank(arr):\n",
    "    order = arr.argsort()\n",
    "    ranks = order.argsort()\n",
    "    return ranks"
   ]
  },

   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# 2. Add Outlier Removal"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 93,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def outlier_removal_data(X, y, percent):\n",
    "    # Train Test Split\n",
    "    x_train_valid, x_test, y_train_valid, y_test = train_test_split(X, y,test_size=0.2,stratify=y, random_state=42)\n",
    "    x_train, x_valid, y_train, y_valid = train_test_split(x_train_valid,y_train_valid,test_size=0.25,stratify=y_train_valid,random_state=42)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Smote\n",
    "    smote = SMOTE()\n",
    "    x_train, y_train = smote.fit_resample(x_train, y_train)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Outlier Detection\n",
    "    from sklearn.neighbors import LocalOutlierFactor\n",
    "    lof = LocalOutlierFactor()\n",
    "\n",
    "    x_outlier = x_train[lof.fit_predict(x_train) == -1]\n",
    "    y_outlier = y_train[lof.fit_predict(x_train) == -1]\n",
    "    x_outlier_df = x_outlier\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Outlier Removal\n",
    "    outlier_rank = rank(abs(lof.negative_outlier_factor_))\n",
    "    shape = x_train.shape[0]\n",
    "    x_train = x_train[outlier_rank <= shape - percent * x_outlier.shape[0]]\n",
    "    y_train = y_train[outlier_rank <= shape - percent * x_outlier.shape[0]]\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Standardize\n",
    "    scaler = StandardScaler()\n",
    "    x_train = scaler.fit_transform(x_train)\n",
    "    x_valid = scaler.transform(x_valid)\n",
    "    x_test = scaler.transform(x_test)\n",
    "    x_outlier = scaler.transform(x_outlier)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # PCA transformation\n",
    "    pca = PCA(n_components=0.99)\n",
    "\n",
    "    x_train = pca.fit_transform(x_train)\n",
    "    x_valid = pca.transform(x_valid)\n",
    "    x_test = pca.transform(x_test)\n",
    "    x_outlier = pca.transform(x_outlier)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return x_train, y_train, x_test, y_test, x_outlier, y_outlier, x_outlier_df"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Logistic with outliers removal"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 21,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "f1_score = []\n",
    "for percent in np.arange(0, 1.05, 0.05):\n",
    "    x_train, y_train, x_test, y_test, x_outlier, y_outlier = outlier_removal_data(X, y, percent)\n",
    "    logreg = LogisticRegression()\n",
    "    logreg = logreg.fit(x_train, y_train)\n",
    "    score = classification_report(y_test, logreg.predict(x_test), output_dict=True)['1']['f1-score']\n",
    "    f1_score.append(score)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 27,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 576x360 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "x_max = np.arange(0, 1.05, 0.05)[np.argmax(f1_score)]\n",
    "y_max = np.max(f1_score)\n",
    "fig = plt.figure(figsize=(8, 5))\n",
    "plt.plot(np.arange(0, 1.05, 0.05), f1_score)\n",
    "plt.plot(x_max, y_max, marker='o', c='r', markersize=10)\n",
    "plt.xlabel(\"x%\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel(\"f1 score for lable 1\")\n",
    "plt.title(\"Outlier Removal Rate v.s. f1-score\")\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Outlier Adjustment and Removal"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 60,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def iqr_rule(series):\n",
    "    percentile_25 = np.quantile(series, 0.25)\n",
    "    percentile_75 = np.quantile(series, 0.75)\n",
    "    iqr = percentile_75 - percentile_25\n",
    "    upper_bound = percentile_75 + 1.5 * iqr\n",
    "    lower_bound = percentile_25 - 1.5 * iqr\n",
    "    series[series > upper_bound] = upper_bound\n",
    "    series[series < lower_bound] = lower_bound\n",
    "    return series"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 61,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def outlier_process(df):\n",
    "    columns = df.columns\n",
    "    for col in columns:\n",
    "        df[col] = iqr_rule(df[col])\n",
    "    return df"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 72,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "x_train_valid, x_test, y_train_valid, y_test = train_test_split(X, y,test_size=0.2,stratify=y, random_state=42)\n",
    "x_train, x_valid, y_train, y_valid = train_test_split(x_train_valid,y_train_valid, test_size=0.25,stratify=y_train_valid,random_state=42)\n",
    "\n",
    "# outlier substitution\n",
    "x_train = outlier_process(x_train)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 73,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "scaler = StandardScaler()\n",
    "x_train = scaler.fit_transform(x_train)\n",
    "x_valid = scaler.transform(x_valid)\n",
    "x_test = scaler.transform(x_test)\n",
    "\n",
    "# smote\n",
    "smote = SMOTE()\n",
    "x_train, y_train = smote.fit_resample(x_train, y_train)\n",
    "\n",
    "#56 principle components account for 99% explained data total variance\n",
    "pca = PCA(n_components=0.99)\n",
    "\n",
    "x_train = pca.fit_transform(x_train)\n",
    "x_valid = pca.transform(x_valid)\n",
    "x_test = pca.transform(x_test)"
   ]
  },
